news.title: GST Council recommendations related to real estate and allied industries
news.para: GST exemption on renting of residential dwelling to business entities (registered persons) has been withdrawn. Sale of land after leveling, laying down of drainage lines etc. is sale of land and does not attract GST.

news.title: Despite reminders, no action on illegal buildings in Ludhiana
news.para: ​The chief vigilance officer has also sought report from the building branch and entire responsibility has been fixed on one of the building inspectors of the said zone.

news.title: Transition period ends amid upkeep worries in Gurugram colonies
news.para: The 15-day transition period during which the developers of these colonies were to assist the civic body ends on the day, but MCG hasn’t deployed any staff to ensure smooth maintenance services, they said.

news.title: Coimbatore corporation ropes in assistant engineers to speed up building plan approvals
news.para: Since there is only an assistant town planning officer for each ward, according to an official source, the civic body has decided to strengthen the building approval process by deploying around 45 engineers at the ward level.

news.title: Nashik civic body brings 13,000 new properties under tax net
news.para: NMC officials said that inclusion of these properties under the tax net will help the civic body to get additional Rs 17 crore property tax every fiscal.

news.title: Not taken over, but Gurugram civic body set to roll out essential services for colony highrises
news.para: The civic body recently took over Sushant Lok-2 and 3, Malibu Towne, Vipul World, Rosewood City, Uppal Southend, Ardee City, Greenwood City and Mayfield Garden.

news.title: Unique ID number for all land parcels in Maharashtra likely by July 15
news.para: Nearly 3 crore existing land parcels, including 2.62 crore 7X12 extracts and 60 lakh city survey property cards, have been allotted random numbers in the testing phase.

news.title: Maharashtra: Two-year extension to convert collector land to freehold
news.para: Federation of Grantees of Government Land (FGGL) had been meeting revenue department officials as well as revenue minister Balasaheb Thorat since August 2021 seeking extension of the scheme that lapsed this March.

news.title: Noida authority directs structural audit of seven buildings next to Supertech twin towers
news.para: This audit, Noida officials clarified, will be an additional exercise, separate from the one by Edifice – the company bringing the towers down – to record all pre-demolition structural defects in residential buildings within 50 metres of the twin towers in Sector 93A.

news.title: From July 1, only online building nod in Maharashtra's civic areas
news.para: "All corporation and council authorities should ensure that the system is in place by July 1. After that, no manual permission should be granted," he said.

news.title: China Vanke says property market has bottomed
news.para: Yu Liang, chairman of China's No.2 developer, cautioned the recovery will be slow and mild, but his comments helped drive the mainland's CSI Real Estate Index up 6%, while Hong Kong's Hang Seng Mainland Properties Index rose over 1%.

news.title: China: S&P upgrades Greenland Holdings days after cutting to 'selective default'
news.para: Last Wednesday, S&P downgraded Shanghai-based Greenland to "selective default", after the firm proposed and later completed a one-year maturity extension of its $500-million bonds originally due on June 25.

news.title: From July 1, Kolhapur civic body to okay all building plans online
news.para: Gagrani visited the KMC headquarters on Monday and interacted with the officials and staff from the town planning department. He also met the developers over several issues pertaining to the building rules and permissions.

news.title: Nisus Finance, BCD Group identify stressed residential assets worth Rs 1,000 crore in Bengaluru
news.para: Nisus and BCD India have signed an agreement to work together on projects. Nisus will bring its financial expertise, and BCD India will bring its technical expertise, sales, and CRM.

news.title: Sobha forms JV to build 2.5 acre housing project in Chennai
news.para: Property consultant Savills India said in a statement that it facilitated a joint development deal for a land parcel of 2.5 acre for Sobha Ltd in Chennai.
